Class TableTabsController

java.lang.Object
comp3111.covid.tabs.TabController
comp3111.covid.tabs.TableTabsController
Direct Known Subclasses:
TabA1pageController, TabB1pageController, TabC1pageController
public abstract class TableTabsController
extends TabController
This is an abstract class representing the controllers of all the tabs that displays tables. This class is inherited by TabA1pageController, TabB1pageController, and TabC1pageController

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      This method initializes items in the tabs. It is called right after all FXML elements are loaded by the application. In TabController, it initializes the CheckListView to show the country name, while internally, it holds a pair containing the country name and the iso code of the location. In TableTabsController, this method is also responsible for setting PropertyValueFactory in each TableColumn in the table.
      Overrides:
      initialize in class TabController

    • updateCheckboxList

      public void updateCheckboxList()
      Description copied from class: TabController
      This initializes the checkboxList after the dataset is imported into the database. It loads the country name - iso code pair into the checkbox list for display, and it adds a (@link javafx.collections.ListChangeListener} to update checked items onece the user clicks on a checkbox.
      Overrides:
      updateCheckboxList in class TabController

    • handleTableError

      protected int handleTableError()
      This method handles user input errors. It handles 3 types of errors: 1. No Country is chosen. 2. No date is selected. 3. The the target date is out of the range of the chosen dataset. A pop-up window with the corresponding message will remind the user of the error.
      Returns:
      a negative integer error code if an error occurs, 0 if no error.

    • generateDataList

      protected java.util.ArrayList<TableTabsController.TableData> generateDataList​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> isoCodes, java.time.LocalDate targetDate)
      This method generate an list of data to be put into the table, with the given user inputs of countries and date.
      Parameters:
      isoCodes - A list of iso codes of the countries that the user has chosen.
      targetDate - The date chosen by the user.
      Returns:
      An ArrayList of TableTabsController.TableData of the given countries and date.

    • generateTable

      protected void generateTable​(java.util.ArrayList<TableTabsController.TableData> data, java.time.LocalDate date)
      This method puts data on the table.
      Parameters:
      data - the list of data to be displayed.
      date - the chosen date, used for the title.

    • getTotalDataFromDB

      protected abstract long getTotalDataFromDB​(java.lang.String isoCode, java.time.LocalDate targetDate)
      This method fetches a value of data of the given location and date from the database. Return value is restricted to be that of cumulative number of cases, deaths, and people fully vaccinated.
      Parameters:
      isoCode - iso code of the chosen location.
      targetDate - date of the user's choice.
      Returns:
      a value of data of the given location and date.

    • getRateDataFromDB

      protected abstract double getRateDataFromDB​(java.lang.String isoCode, java.time.LocalDate targetDate)
      This method fetches a value of data of the given location and date from the database. Return value is restricted to be that of cumulative number of cases per 1M people, deaths per 1M people, and rate of vaccination.
      Parameters:
      isoCode - iso code of the chosen location
      targetDate - date of the user's choice
      Returns:
      a value of the given parameters.

    • setTableTitle

      protected abstract void setTableTitle()
      This method sets the title of the table according to the type of the tab.

    • getTableData

      protected abstract TableTabsController.TableData getTableData​(java.lang.String iso, long totalData, double rateData)
      This method constructs a TableTabsController.TableData object with the given parameters. Depending of the type of the tab, a percentage sign % may be added to the back of rate data during the construction.
      Parameters:
      iso - Iso code of the desired location.
      totalData - Value for the second column.
      rateData - Value for the third column.
      Returns:
      A TableTabsController.TableData object consisting of the above values.
